{"lemma":"أَجْرَدانِ","slug":"أَجْرَدانِ","root":"ج.ر.د","root_slug":"ج-ر-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-ر-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n5487","n5488"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"barren, bare of vegetation, without herbage","examples":[{"text":"أَرْضٌ جَرْدَاء، لَا طَعَامَ وَلَا مَاء، يَا إِلٰهِي!"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"unarmed or unshielded, stripped of what could protect"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"hairless, bald"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Color or defect adjective from the root ج ر د (j r d)."},"ipa":["/ʔad͡ʒ.rad/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n5487","headword_ar":"اَجْرَدُ","root":"jrd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no hair upon him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, L, K;) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon his body;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"except in certain parts, as the line along the middle of the bosom and downwards to the belly, and the arms from the elbows downwards, and the legs from the knees downwards; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oEaru","text_ar":"اَشْعَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which signifies “having hair upon the whole of the body:” (IAth, L:) [fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jarodaA='u","text_ar":"جَرْدَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jurodN","text_ar":"جُرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, TA.) The people of Paradise are said (in a trad., TA) to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jurodN murodN","text_ar":"جُرْدٌ مُرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having no hair upon their bodies,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beardless"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also applied to a horse, (S, A, K,) and any similar beast, (TA,) meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having short hair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having short and fine hair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) This is approved, (S,) and is one of the signs of an excellent and a generous origin. (TA.) Pl. as above. (A.) In like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajoradu AlqawaAy^imi","text_ar":"اَجْرَدُ القَوَايِمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having short,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"short and fine, hair upon the legs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  Also (tropical:)  A check"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon which no hair has grown."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And (assumed tropical:)  A sandal"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon which is no hair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L from a trad.) ―         -b4-  Applied also to a place; and the fem.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jarodaA='u","text_ar":"جَرْدَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", to land: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaridN","text_ar":"جَرِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. ―         -b5-  Also (tropical:)  Milk"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from froth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And the fem., (assumed tropical:)  Wine that is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from dregs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, TA.) And (assumed tropical:)  A sky"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from clouds."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b6-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Smooth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 413.) ―         -b7-  (assumed tropical:)  A heart"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from concealed hatred, and from deceit, dishonesty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dissimulation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b8-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Complete;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from deficiency;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jariydN","text_ar":"جَرِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, K;) applied to a year ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAmN","text_ar":"عَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (S, A,) and to a month, (Th, TA,) and to a day: (K:) fem. as above, applied to a year ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sanapN","text_ar":"سَنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (A.) Accord. to Ks, (S,) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA raA^ayotuhu mu*o","text_ar":"مَا رَاَيْتُهُ مُذْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajoradaAni","text_ar":"اَجْرَدَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m* jariydaAni","text_ar":"مذ جَرِيدَانِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have not seen him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, for,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"during,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two days,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two months,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two years,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"complete."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b9-  (tropical:)  A horse"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wont to outstrip others;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that outstrips others, and becomes separate from them by his swiftness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IJ, TA.) ―         -b10-  And the fem., (tropical:)  A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"voracious"},{"kind":"text","text":"she-camel. (A.)       -A2-  It is also used as a subst.: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaradN","text_ar":"جَرَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b2-  and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljurodaAnu","text_ar":"الجُرْدَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  Also (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sea."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AAF, M in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jrb","text_ar":"جرب"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-  And the fem., (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A smooth rock."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["IAth","L","S","A","K","TA","AHn","Th"]},{"entry_id":"n5488","headword_ar":"اـِجْرِدٌّ","root":"jrd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", and sometimes without teshdeed,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ijoridN","text_ar":"اـِجْرِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain plant which indicates the places where truffles"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamoA^ap","text_ar":"كَمْاَة"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are to be found: a certain herb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leguminous plant, said to have grains like pepper."},{"kind":"text","text":"(En-Nadr, TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}